definition: to have/there is/there are/to exist/to be
haven't/hasn't/doesn't exist/to not have/to not be
to have sth to do with/to relate to/related to/to concern/concerning
someone/people/anyone/there is someone there/occupied (as in restroom)

sentences.english: Still, who are we to say that we can stay?
sentences.chinese: 然而，誰有敢說我們能長留此地？

sentences.english: It's necessary for us to net the currant bushes.
sentences.chinese: 我們有必要用網蓋上紅醋栗樹。

sentences.english: As soon as you prove to be good, you will get more followers.
sentences.chinese: 如果事實證明你還不錯，必定會有更多追隨者。

sentences.english: I grant that yours are of better quality.
sentences.chinese: 我授與你的是有較好的質量。

sentences.english: The results have important guiding significance on the production safety of fertilizer-related enterprises.
sentences.chinese: 研究結果對相關化肥企業的安全生產有指導意義。

sentences.english: All these writers run to sentiment.
sentences.chinese: 所有這些作家都有傷感的傾向。

sentences.english: EarthSound's products have an excellent track record in the States.
sentences.chinese: 天籟的產品在美國有非常輝煌的過去。

sentences.english: His talking is full of speculative thinking, it sounds quite logical.
sentences.chinese: 講話的思辨性極強，聽起來很有邏輯。

sentences.english: Digital image steganography does have some drawbacks, though.
sentences.chinese: 但是，數碼圖像隱寫術仍然有一定缺點。

sentences.english: J: You have a very busy life. Lots of a week activies.
sentences.chinese: 你生活很充實啊，有很多的活動。

sentences.english: And you express that "I'm feeling this way, is it ok?"
sentences.chinese: 你可以表達“我有這樣子的感覺，沒問題吧？”

sentences.english: Xylitol also appears to have potential as a treatment for osteoporosis.
sentences.chinese: 木糖醇似乎有治癒骨質疏鬆的潛力。

sentences.english: Father Mabeuf was one of those persons for whom plants have souls.
sentences.chinese: 和某些人一樣，馬白夫公公也認爲植物是有靈魂的。

sentences.english: They must have strong longings that lures them to attend MEC.
sentences.chinese: 他們一定有很強烈的渴望促使他們參加英語角。

sentences.english: What sequela is there after becoming gall-stone operation?
sentences.chinese: 做了膽結石手術後有什麼後遺症嗎？

definition: of/~'s (possessive particle)/(used after an attribute)/(used to form a nominal expression)/(used at the end of a declarative sentence for emphasis)
haven't/hasn't/doesn't exist/to not have/to not be
and/together with/with/sum/union/peace/harmony/Taiwan pr. [han4] when it means "and" or "with"
to combine a powdery substance (flour, plaster etc) with water/Taiwan pr. [huo4]
to complete a set in mahjong or playing cards
to compose a poem in reply (to sb's poem) using the same rhyme sequence/to join in the singing/to chime in with others
to mix (ingredients) together/to blend/classifier for rinses of clothes/classifier for boilings of medicinal herbs
variant of 是[shi4]/(used in given names)
I've got a solution!/to have a bun in the oven (abbr. for 有了胎[you3 le5 tai1])
this/these/(commonly pr. [zhei4] before a classifier, esp. in Beijing)
also/too/(in Classical Chinese) final particle implying affirmation
like that/in that way/or so/so/so very much/about/in that case
